# Helm/K8s manifests and policy-as-test inputs MUST check out and render with LF
# line endings. Under core.autocrlf=true these files were materialized CRLF in the
# working tree, so `helm template` emitted CRLF and conftest's YAML splitter
# collapsed the multi-doc render to a SINGLE evaluated document — every deny rule
# silently passed (a false-green gate). Pinning eol=lf here keeps the rendered
# manifest LF so each rendered document is evaluated independently (ADR-0029 §5).
*.yaml text eol=lf
*.yml  text eol=lf
*.rego text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
# Policy-as-test BITE harnesses (e.g. policy/fixtures/run-pg-hba-bite.sh) are bash
# and MUST stay LF — a CRLF shebang/line breaks the script under core.autocrlf=true
# (mirrors ci/.gitattributes for the kind-harness scripts).
*.sh   text eol=lf
